<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> <h1><a name="FSSStorage_Management"></a>  <strong><noop>FSSStorage Management</strong> </h1>
<div class="twikiToc"> <ul>
<li> <a href="?cover=print#Making_Allocations"> Making Allocations</a> <ul>
<li> <a href="?cover=print#Storage_Area_Registration"> Storage Area Registration</a>
</li> <li> <a href="?cover=print#Public_Storage_Monitoring"> Public Storage Monitoring</a>
</li> <li> <a href="?cover=print#Requesting_an_Allocation"> Requesting an Allocation</a>
</li> <li> <a href="?cover=print#Granting_Allocations"> Granting Allocations</a>
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> <a href="?cover=print#Changing_an_Allocation"> Changing an Allocation</a>
</li> <li> <a href="?cover=print#Allocation_or_Dataset_Cleanup_by"> Allocation or Dataset Cleanup by a VO</a>
</li> <li> <a href="?cover=print#Allocation_or_Dataset_Cleanup_us"> Allocation or Dataset Cleanup using the Operations Toolkit</a>
</li></ul> 
</div>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Making_Allocations"></a> Making Allocations </span></h2>
<p />
<p />
These steps are needed.
<p />
<h3><a name="Storage_Area_Registration"></a> Storage Area Registration </h3>
<p />
Each OSG Storage Element participating in opportunistic storage is registered by the OSG production coordinator in the allocation database. 
<p /> <ol>
<li> The PC runs an OSG Discovery Tool <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_discovery_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">storage area discovery utility</a> of the PC Utilities to discover storage areas which qualify as public storage. 
</li> <li> Upon verification, the PC runs a <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_registration_utilit" class="twikiAnchorLink">storage area registration utility</a> which saves the output of the tool into the Storage Area Registry of the Allocation Accounting Service for every VO that has installed the AAS and requested storage. 
</li> <li> The PC runs the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_registry_broadcast" class="twikiAnchorLink">storage area registry broadcast tool</a> to propagate that information to all other AAS instances. 
</li> <li> The PC runs the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_registration_test_u" class="twikiAnchorLink">storage area registration test utility</a>, which verifies that the above information has been successfully entered in the databases.
</li></ol> 
<p />
<h3><a name="Public_Storage_Monitoring"></a> Public Storage Monitoring </h3>
<p />
The step is needed to support public storage allocation. These actions could be performed by a VOA-owned cron job
<p /> <ol>
<li> The Pigeon Tool <a href="http://home.fnal.gov/~dstrain/pigeon" target="_top">storage area verification tool</a> of the VOA Utilities is invoked by the VOA.
</li> <li> The verification tool updates the VO’s Access Record Repository Catalog (ARR) with the discovery and access results using the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Storage_resource_update_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">storage resource update utility</a>. 
</li></ol> 
<p />
<h3><a name="Requesting_an_Allocation"></a> Requesting an Allocation </h3>
<p /> <ol>
<li> To request an allocation, the VOA communicates with the PC, and includes the following information.
</li>  </ol><ul>
<li> The size of the allocation
</li> <li> The needed lifetime of the allocation. The expiration time of the allocation will be set using this lifetime and the time that the allocation is made.
</li> <li> Optionally, other requirements pertaining to the site’s storage and compute resources.
</li></ul> 
<p />
The VOA may use the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_request_tool" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation request tool</a> to assist in composing the request.
<p />
<p />
<h3><a name="Granting_Allocations"></a> Granting Allocations </h3>
<p />
When a VO requests space, an allocation must be done on a registered storage area.
<p /> <ol>
<li> The PC runs the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_decision_tool" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation decision tool</a> that shows the PC the storage areas that could meet the allocation request.
</li> <li> The PC selects a storage resource which meets the needs of the allocation.
</li> <li> The PC enters the allocation into the AAS of every VO using the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_update_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation update utility</a>. This redundancy serves as a backup in case the VO loses its AAS database. 
</li> <li> The PC checks that the allocation has been successfully entered by running the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_info_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">storage area info utility</a>.
</li> <li> The VOA confirms the allocation by running the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_test_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation test utility</a>.
</li></ol> 
<p /> <ul>
<li> Diagram of operations to make an allocation <br />     <img src="https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/twiki/pub/Storage/OSGPublicStorage/pub_storage_1.jpg" alt="pub_storage_1.jpg" width='800' height='600' />    
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Changing_an_Allocation"></a> Changing an Allocation </span></h2>
<p /> <ol>
<li> The VOA communicates to the PC a request to release, resize, or change the lifetime of an allocation. The VOA may use the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_request_tool" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation request tool</a> to assist in composing the request. If the request is to release an allocation, it should first be cleaned up (see below).
</li> <li> The PC uses the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Storage_area_info_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">storage area info utility</a> to decide whether the request can be met.
</li> <li> The PC uses the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_update_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation update utility</a> to change the corresponding attribute on the allocation object in the AAS of every VO.
</li></ol> 
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Allocation_or_Dataset_Cleanup_by"></a> Allocation or Dataset Cleanup by a VO </span></h2>
<p />
Allocations are normally kept clean by users defining collections of files called "datasets", and deleting datasets when they expire or are no longer needed. See
<p /> <ol>
<li> The VOA or user calls the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_cleanup_tool" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation cleanup tool</a> or the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Dataset_cleanup_tool" class="twikiAnchorLink">dataset cleanup tool</a>. The allocation  cleanup tool does the following.
</li>  </ol><ul>
<li> The tool checks the expiration attribute of every allocation object
</li> <li> For every expired allocation, it finds all datasets that refer to the allocation. This includes the default dataset for files that are not in any other dataset.
</li> <li> It deletes each dataset using the dataset operation tool.
</li></ul> 
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Allocation_or_Dataset_Cleanup_us"></a> Allocation or Dataset Cleanup using the Operations Toolkit </span></h2>
<p />
If a VO does not clean up.
<p /> <ol>
<li> The PC checks for expired allocations using the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_query_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation query utility</a>. 
</li> <li> The PC may work with the VOA of an expired allocation to extend the lifetime of the allocation, or to have the VO remove its files.
</li></ol> 
<p />
Otherwise, the following steps are done
<p /> <ol>
<li> The PC runs a tool to construct a list of site file names of all the files in the expired allocation.
</li> <li> The PC forwards the list of site file names to the site administrator.
</li> <li> The site administrator examines the list to try to ensure that no harm will be done by the deletions.
</li> <li> The site administrator executes the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Public_storage_cleanup_tool" class="twikiAnchorLink">public storage cleanup tool</a> using the list as input.
</li> <li> The site administrator informs the PC that the files have been deleted.
</li> <li> The PC uses the <a href="/bin/view/Storage/FSSCommandReference#Allocation_update_utility" class="twikiAnchorLink">allocation update utility</a> to set the space used attribute of the allocation object to zero in all AAS instances.
</li></ol> 
<p />
-- <a href="/bin/view/Main/TedHesselroth" class="twikiLink">TedHesselroth</a> - 20 Sep 2010</div><!-- /patternTopic-->
